        <p>Hayao Miyazaki (宮崎 駿, Miyazaki Hayao, [mijaꜜzaki hajaꜜo]; born 5 January 1941)
            is a Japanese animator, director, producer, screenwriter, author,
            and manga artist. A co-founder of Studio Ghibli, a film and animation studio,
            he has attained international acclaim as a masterful storyteller and as a maker
            of animated feature films, and is widely regarded as one of the most accomplished
            filmmakers in the history of animation.</p>
